column5: 3724 miles round trip, Eugene, OR to Ft. Frances then fly in.

Our group drives just a shade over 2800 miles on our way thru 5 states and than we jump on a float plane and fly 3 hours to some of the biggest, meanest Pike, Lake trout and Walleye that man has ever set a hook on.
I had a customer from Rome, Italy last season. Not sure if that counts since he had to take a plane to Chicago, then drive up from there. Agate
We drive 2450 miles round trip...and that is plenty. We fish at Lac Seul and the drive is well worth it for getting to fish the best Walleye lake in canada.
My Dad and I travel 1600 miles round trip...doesn't seem so far now, compared to you other guys!
Two years ago drove from Las Vegas to Chicago then on to Red Lake 2600 plus miles one way. 5200 plus miles round trip. I am flying into Thunder Bay this year and being picked up by my friends Larry S
We drive 2150 miles round trip from Eastern Ohio to Nakina.
We drive about 2400 miles round trip to Lac Seul, also from eastern ohio. Can't wait!!!!!

My son will fly from West Palm Beach,Florida to Winnipeg and we will fly on to Great Bear Lake NWT, then fly to the Coppermine River for a day and fish the lake for the rest of the week.......Round trip for him about 8,500 air miles........
we drive 3300 round trip from west virginia .in the usa.21 days left ...stayin at evergreen lodge
